<subSubSection id="CDB2699AED8CDDFE924E8F48AC976372" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="338ABF604464C046612526DEC469DC56" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4E966D37BEDCD3370E49C234D44868FE" LSID="46FF2912-4E88-51E3-9D74-78994611469F" authority="Jeannel, 1941" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1941" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Peryphanes)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Peryphanes">Peryphanes Jeannel, 1941</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="03AD131E1E0C52C52673F693F16B7BC6" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="DECBE0642E765ED5A2646502C573B8C4" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">
<taxonomicName id="807E975AED0D22D62E80180FB2A6E182" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1941" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Peryphanes</taxonomicName>
Jeannel, 1941b: 484. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="8E858C73EFB331C7557C33124ED95ECF" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dalmatinus">
<emphasis id="7F78753D2DD3565EBE92D9AA626E3DD5" italics="true" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">Peryphus dalmatinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 by original designation. Etymology. Uncertain, possibly from the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="B5A8D8AE6D401EFB6E1612951ECC5C8A" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="924467740738643774CEF4DCF3173BAC" italics="true" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">Peryphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="E146F166A3DF2865070C229A8090CC94" italics="true" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">q.v</emphasis>
.] contracted and the Greek 
<emphasis id="C58890E8EA05516631DA7E1AE6434AA7" italics="true" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">phanos</emphasis>
(light, bright) [feminine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BC561C89C49DFAA6B321D0702419549E" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="22C8B848BA2A8ECF6F85E02F0D7A36D1" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6FF2C71BFC26F93EC2D37F9B6D1F3E6A" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">
Northern Hemisphere, with about 35 species in the Nearctic (seven species, one of them adventive) and Palaearctic (about 30 species) Regions. Two species (
<taxonomicName id="8E32AD84F4EDA4950A33E214A92DBE05" authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1827" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grapii">
<emphasis id="39DB91291FA22969B318DD6C74078AA0" italics="true" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">Bembidion grapii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="92BACC6433A9E4AEED38A7A44EC446D9" authorityName="Fall" authorityYear="1926" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yukonum">
<emphasis id="8056342D043E00BB60B7E0DFFE1CFE5F" italics="true" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">Bembidion yukonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), placed in this subgenus for convenience, are Holarctic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ADC56293A0E1D2E27B43E2F23D340D67" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" type="identification">
<paragraph id="AAB0B061C780956E45A4DFD90C16A1B7" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1504C8B3A2E49B208FC1EFC2D51C7910" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">
Lindroth (1963b) covered all but one (
<taxonomicName id="472025BAA08FFAC67E7C31EA7E69A736" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1897" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="377" pageNumber="378" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subangustatum">
<emphasis id="A9BB88A298D7F6BCC22315FC3AA7CFEC" italics="true" pageId="377" pageNumber="378">Bembidion subangustatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) of the species found in North America.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
